{"TopicId":174184,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Are Landing Legs Bugged in 1.4.1?","CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-22T18:36:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-22T18:36:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTitle says it all.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-22T18:51:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. Supposedly gonna be fixed 1.4.3.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aptiva","CreatedById":187683,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-22T20:35:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat exactly is buggy about them?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-22T23:12:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223361307\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221524429313\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187683\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aptiva\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Aptiva said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat exactly is buggy about them?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have a multi-stage craft\u00A0where one of the stages is a lander, and you decouple the lander and land it all in one go -- then the landing legs will tend to explode. If you switch focus away from the lander to any other ship or to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E or save the game and reload it, then the legs will work correctly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe same problem happens with rovers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-22T23:13:05Z\u0022 title=\u002204/22/2018 11:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by bewing\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-23T00:37:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, I didn\u0027t realize there was a way to defuse the landing legs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lego_Prodigy","CreatedById":187421,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-23T00:38:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo Right now I can have explosive lander fun? And you DIDNT tell me?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SchitzoSchaf","CreatedById":185318,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-23T11:14:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nanother quick and dirty fix is to bring up the crash tolerance up to 60 \u002B in the game files (stock its around 12 or 10 for mk3) files found in gamedata\\squad\\parts\\utility\\LandingLegLT-X\\LandingLegLT-X.cfg where X is the number of the item tier (1-3) change the value crashtollerance inside the cfg to something like 60 to 120 as you like\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}